<item>
            <title>[POOL-199] GOP/GKOP evict() method is not synchronised and is not thread-safe</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/POOL-199</link>
                <project id="12310488" key="POOL">Commons Pool</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The evict() method in Pool2 GOP/GKOP classes is not synchronised, yet it relies on accessing and updating the field evictionIterator without any synchronisation.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Adding volatile to the field would help with safe publication across threads, but won&apos;t address the problem of two evictions running in parallel.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;AFAICT, two threads running evict() in parallel could operate on the same objects, which will almost certainly cause problems.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The evict() method should probably be synchronised, which would also solve the safe publication problem.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
